<section class="my-8">
  <h2 class="mb-4">When to use this component</h2>
  <p>Use the radio component when you need to help users select a single option from a list.</p>
</section>

<section class="mb-8">
  <h2 class="mb-4">When not to use this component</h2>
  <p>Do not use the radios component if users can choose more than one option from a list. In this case, use the <a href="/components/checkbox">checkboxes</a> component.</p>
</section>

<section class="mb-8">
  <h2 class="mb-4">How to use this component</h2>
  <p>Radios are grouped within a <code>fieldset</code> which starts with a <code>legend</code> which lets the user know what they need to do.</p>
</section>

<section class="mb-8">
  <h2 class="mb-4">Variants</h2>

  <h3 class="mb-4">Descriptions</h3>
  <p>This variant allows you to add more context to the options in the list. The description is populated by providing a <code>description</code> parameter within the radio’s <code>label</code> parameter.</p>
  {{ example({group: "components", item: "radios", example: "with-descriptions", html: true, open: false }) }}

  <h3 class="mb-4">Other</h3>
  <p>This variant lets the user provide an answer other to the options in the list, or to provide supplemental information required to describe the nature of their answer.</p>
  <p>The radio label must be directly followed by the <code>radio__description</code> to let the user know they will need to provide an answer if they select this option.</p>
  <p>Use this variation by wrapping the text field in a div with class <code>radio__other</code>, added directly after the radio label. CSS hides this field until the radio is <code>:checked</code>.</p>
  {{ example({group: "components", item: "radios", example: "other", html: true, open: false }) }}

  <h3 class="mb-4">Other - visible input</h3>
  <p>This variant of the ‘Other’ radio input type shows the input instead of waiting for the radio to be <code>:checked</code>. This variant does not require the <code>radio__description</code> to be present.</p>
  {{ example({group: "components", item: "radios", example: "other--visible-input", html: true, open: false }) }}

  <h3 class="mb-4">Other - select</h3>
  <p>This variant of the ‘Other’ radio input type uses a select instead of an input. Select “pepperoni” for select to become visible.</p>
  {{ example({group: "components", item: "radios", example: "other--select", html: true, open: false }) }}

  <h3 class="mb-4">Radios with an ‘or’ label</h3>
